<%= faq_schema([
  { question: "How do I calculate cost per mile for my car?", answer: "Add up all annual vehicle costs: fuel, insurance, maintenance, depreciation, registration, and financing. Divide the total by miles driven in the same period. For example, if annual costs total $8,000 and you drive 12,000 miles, your cost per mile is $8,000 / 12,000 = $0.667 per mile." },
  { question: "What is the average cost per mile for a car?", answer: "According to AAA, the average cost per mile for a new car is approximately $0.60 to $0.80, including fuel, insurance, maintenance, depreciation, financing, and registration. Smaller sedans cost less per mile ($0.50-0.60), while trucks and SUVs cost more ($0.70-1.00). Used cars generally have lower per-mile costs due to reduced depreciation." },
  { question: "What costs should I include in cost per mile?", answer: "Include all vehicle-related expenses: fuel costs, insurance premiums, routine maintenance (oil changes, tires, brakes), repairs, depreciation (the decrease in vehicle value), financing or lease payments, registration and taxes, parking, and tolls. For a comprehensive picture, include every dollar you spend related to owning and operating the vehicle." },
  { question: "How does depreciation affect cost per mile?", answer: "Depreciation is often the largest component of cost per mile, especially for new vehicles. A new car can lose 20-30% of its value in the first year and about 15% per year after that. On a $35,000 car driven 12,000 miles per year, first-year depreciation of $10,000 adds $0.83 per mile. This is why used cars have a lower total cost per mile." },
  { question: "How do I use cost per mile for the IRS mileage deduction?", answer: "The IRS sets a standard mileage rate for business use of personal vehicles, which was $0.67 per mile for 2024. You can either use this standard rate or calculate your actual per-mile costs. If your actual cost per mile exceeds the IRS rate, itemizing actual expenses may provide a larger deduction. Keep detailed records of all expenses and miles driven." }
]) %>

